<CanvasGradient>
<summary>
The <strong><c>CanvasGradient</c></strong> interface represents an <see href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opaque_data_type">opaque object</see> describing a gradient. It is returned by the methods <see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateLinearGradient"/>, <see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateConicGradient"/> or <see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateRadialGradient"/>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>It can be used as a <see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D.FillStyle"/> or <see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D.StrokeStyle"/>.</para>
<para>-Creator methods in <see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D"/>.<br/>-The {{HTMLElement("canvas")}} element and its associated interface, <see cref="HTMLCanvasElement"/>.<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasGradient"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CanvasGradient>
<CanvasGradientAddColorStop>
<summary>
The <strong><c>CanvasGradient.addColorStop()</c></strong> method adds a new color stop,<br/>defined by an <c>offset</c> and a <c>color</c>, to a given canvas gradient.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-The interface defining this method: <see cref="CanvasGradient"/><br/>-<see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateLinearGradient"/><br/>-<see cref="CanvasRenderingContext2D.CreateRadialGradient"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CanvasGradient/addColorStop"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<returns>None (<see cref="Undefined"/>).</returns>
</CanvasGradientAddColorStop>
